TLDR: I think Dream should address his fanbase to help people be less toxic.

I just really think that this sort of thing needs to be addressed, and it be kept under control.

I'm saying this as someone who got into mcyt around March of 2020, and who really enjoyed watching Dream's videos, and this is just my opinion.

set clear boundaries and told their fans if something was not right. They address the problem, and because Dream's never really addressed it, more fueling the fire if anything (and it may be by accident, I can't know what's happening in his head), it's gotten so out of control. +

And of course, it's not just dttwt, there's a lot of really negative aspects of every subtwt, and while some are better at calling it out because they're smaller, it still doesn't help. The only places where you don't really find it is where CC's have specifically +

messed up too: no matter what one of them says, they get called hot for it, people headcanoning real people (which you can't do), the amount of names that have some form of fetishization or sexual tone with their username slapped on, it goes on. +

that is most definitely not just surface level. The shipping for the most part seems really basic, but doing even just a little digging and you get so much messed up stuff that it's seriously toxic. 

The heavy sexualisation that a lot of minors do for DT is honestly +

Don't know how to properly word this, but I think Dream should take a step back from Twitter for a bit or at least just see a lot of the stuff that happens on here. 

While a lot of negative stuff is pretty surface level, there's also a heavy amount of stuff +
